description.plain: Regarded as the “King of Latin Pop”, Enrique Iglesias is a bilingual singer, songwriter, actor, and music producer. He was born in Madrid, Spain with two older siblings and a father who was also a popular musician, Julio Iglesias. Enrique started his career in 1995 on a Spanish American record label– Fonovisa Records. Around five years after his start Enrique had made a successful crossover into American mainstream music and signed a $68 million dollar contract with Universal Music Latin Entertainment for Spanish music releases and Interscope Records for English music releases. Connecting strongly with both music markets, Enrique was something beyond what the average artist could offer at the time. After making many of his greatest hits with these two labels, in 2015 Iglesias signed with Sony Music. As of 2017 Iglesias has over 150 number one hits across all of the Billboard charts and has sold over 159 million records— making him one of the best selling Spanish artists of all time.

description.plain:
“Bailando” is a 2014 single by Enrique Iglesias originally written by Cuban musicians Descemer Bueno and the popular reggaeton act Gente De Zona in 2013. For the new version of the track, Enrique added vocals to the original and it became a worldwide smash, hitting as high as #12 on the Billboard Hot 100—Enrique’s highest-charting Spanish language single—and has currently spent 28 weeks atop Billboard’s Hot Latin Songs chart.

The video was released April 11, 2014.

songs.title_with_featured: SÚBEME LA RADIO (Ft. Descemer Bueno & Zion & Lennox)

description.plain:
‘Súbeme La Radio’ es una canción de Enrique Iglesias que cuenta con la colaboración de Descemer Bueno, con quien ya colaboró en ‘Bailando’, y del dúo Zion & Lennox.

Se trata de un tema festivo con aires de reggaeton y un estribillo pegadizo en el que los cuatro artistas cantan a un amor pasado y a la fiesta como mejor terapia.

El vídeo para la canción se grabó en La Habana, Cuba, en la segunda semana de enero de 2017.

El primer avance de la canción se pudo escuchar a través de un vídeo del rodaje publicado en Instagram.

A través de Twitter, Enrique estrenó un fragmento del vídeo que se ha rodado en Cuba:

https://twitter.com/enriqueiglesias/status/824355576981229568

description.plain:
En “EL BAÑO”, Enrique habla de conocer a una chica poco a poco antes de una relación seria. Prefiere disfrutar el tiempo con ella bañándose, bailando, yendo al cine y teniendo sexo juntos. Bad Bunny también destaca el sentimiento emocional y sexual entre los dos amantes.

Esta canción marca la primera colaboración entre Enrique Iglesias y el rapero Bad Bunny.
